                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50/2437: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-25T20:00:00-04:30"
                            >August 25, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 26—4:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>761. My 727, August 13, 8 p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d49fn27">Not printed.</note>
                    During a conversation today with Foreign Minister Parra Perez, inquired his
                    views concerning the Colombian proposal for the formation of a bloc. The
                    Minister replied that he is now examining the Colombian proposal with
                    [President] Medina who only yesterday returned to his office from an inspection
                    of the flooded areas. The Minister expressed his own view that such matters
                    should be dealt with on a Pan-American basis rather than through blocs. This has
                    been the tenor of press editorial comment in recent days.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Bogotá.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
